\section*{Atrial Fibrillation (aFib)}
- Uniquely characterized by an absence of P-waves before the QRS complex
- HR: Highly irregular with significant fluctuation
- Treatment: beta-blockers (Metoprolol, Sotalol, etc.), Ca++ channel blockers (Diltiazem, Verapamil, etc.), Digoxin, synchronized cardioversion.
