\section*{Atrial Flutter}
- Uniquely characterized by a saw-toothed flutter appearance
- Toothed fluttering represents multiple P -waves for a single QRS complex
- Treatment: synchronized cardioversion, beta-blockers (Metoprolol, Sotalol, etc.), Ca++ channel blockers (Diltiazem, Verapamil, etc), Atrial Flutter.
