\section*{Ventricular Tachycardia (vTach)}
- Abnormally-patterned wide QRS complex
- No P-waves
- High likelihood of rapid deterioration to a state of ventricular fibrillation (vFib)
- HR: >100 BPM
- Treatment: Defibrillation
